# Financial Dashboard Backend Documentation

This document provides a deep, technical analysis of the **Expenses**, **Contributions**, and **Dashboard** modules within the E-commerce Backend API.

---

## 1. Expenses Module

### Overview
The Expenses module handles the creation, updating, retrieval, and deletion of business expenses. Expenses are evaluated securely through role-based guards and integrated deeply with the [Transaction](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#289-313) (Ledger) and `ActivityAuditLog` systems to maintain strict financial compliance.

### Data Model ([Expense](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/expense.controller.ts#97-167))
- **Primary Keys:** 
  - [id](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/expense.controller.ts#262-309) (BigInt) - Internal relational ID.
  - `publicId` (UUID) - External facing ID used by API clients.
  - `expenseId` (String) - Business-facing auto-generated format `#FIX001` or `#OPE001` depending on the `ExpenseType`.
- **Fields:** 
  - `expenseType` (FIXED | OPERATIONAL)
  - `amount`, `expenseDate`, `dueDate`, `status` (PENDING | APPROVED | PAID | REJECTED)
  - `recurring` (Boolean), `frequency` (monthly | yearly)
- **Relationships:** Belongs to a creator (`createdBy`) and optionally a payer (`paidBy`). Has many [Transaction](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#289-313) entries seamlessly maintaining double-entry-like ledger trails.

### Key Endpoints & Logic ([src/routes/expense.routes.ts](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/routes/expense.routes.ts))
- **`POST /api/expenses`**: (Admin restricted). Creates an expense. Auto-generates `expenseId` incrementally based on `FIXED`/`OPERATIONAL`. **Critical Logic**: If the created expense has the status `"PAID"`, it concurrently commits a `DEBIT` transaction in the ledger inside a Prisma transaction block.
- **`GET /api/expenses`**: Fetches paginated expense records. Supports versatile query filtering by `category`, `status`, and `expenseType`. Calculates an `overdueByDays` property dynamically on-the-fly depending on the `dueDate` relative to the exact current time.
- **`GET /api/expenses/:publicId`**: Fetches a single expense encompassing all relational `transactions` arrays and payer ([Account](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#113-129) / `UserProfile`) details.
- **`PUT /api/expenses/:publicId`**: (Admin restricted). Updates expense metadata and strictly captures an `UPDATE` event inside the `ActivityAuditLog` table.
- **`PATCH /api/expenses/:publicId/pay`**: (Admin restricted). Transitions an expense to the `"PAID"` status. Generates a fresh `DEBIT` transaction in the ledger representing the cash outflow seamlessly within atomic Prisma transactions.
- **`DELETE /api/expenses/:publicId`**: (Admin restricted). Implements a defensive **soft-delete** paradigm. If financial `transactions` are discovered associated with the expense, the backend rejects the hard-delete and advises the client to mark it as `REJECTED` instead. For safe deletions, it sets status to `REJECTED`.

---

## 2. Contributions Module

### Overview
The Contributions module acts as the authoritative source tracking capital injected directly into the business domain (e.g., from founding stakeholders or owners), keeping these sums cleanly segregated from standard operational revenue.

### Data Model ([Contribution](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/contribution.controller.ts#56-79))
- **Keys:** [id](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/expense.controller.ts#262-309) (BigInt), `publicId` (UUID)
- **Fields:** `contributorName`, `amount`, `contributionDate`, `notes`, `color` (specifically allocated for front-end tracking & chart segregation)
- **Relationships:** Links to an [Account](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#113-129) for immutable auditing (`createdBy`). Has a strict 1-to-many relationship mapping into [Transaction](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#289-313) (Ledger).

### Key Endpoints & Logic ([src/routes/contribution.routes.ts](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/routes/contribution.routes.ts))
- **`POST /api/contributions`**: (Admin restricted). Registers a contribution. **Critical Logic**: A corresponding `CREDIT` transaction is rigorously enforced within the ledger under the dedicated `CAPITAL` transaction category.
- **`GET /api/contributions`**: Efficiently serves a paginated collection of all contributions. Harnesses flexible filtering capable of fuzzy searching by `contributorName` combined simultaneously with date/amount sorting.
- **`GET /api/contributions/:publicId`**: Acquires a monolithic contribution alongside its ledger transaction footprint.
- **`PUT /api/contributions/:publicId`**: (Admin restricted). Mutates business details (amounts, customized colors, notes) securely, binding to the `ActivityAuditLog` with `action: UPDATE`.
- **`DELETE /api/contributions/:publicId`**: (Admin restricted). Enforces referential integrity. Actively halts deletion if irreversible ledger `transactions` exist.

---

## 3. Dashboard Module

### Overview
A computationally intensive, read-only analytical module providing macro-level business intelligence. It effectively stitches and aggregates scattered metrics across transactions, expenses, invoices, and contributions, funneling optimized insights to the client.

### Key Endpoints & Logic ([src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts))

- **`GET /api/dashboard/overview`**
  - Complex analytical endpoint pivoting primarily around temporal `from` and `to` date boundaries (defaulting to Current vs Previous Month).
  - Isolates and aggregates `CREDIT` versus `DEBIT` volumes to derive precise `netProfit` boundaries.
  - Aggregates strictly `"PAID"` expenses split across `FIXED` vs `OPERATIONAL` matrices.
  - Executes comprehensive ratio math dynamically transmitting percentage deviations (Change / Prev) for KPIs including: `revenueChange`, `expenseChange`, `fixedCostsChange`, `operationalCostsChange`, and `expenditureChange`.

- **`GET /api/dashboard/account-balance`**
  - High-performance streamlined endpoint that rapidly summarizes all `CREDIT` variants minus all `DEBIT` variants, yielding direct corporate liquidity (Balance).

- **`GET /api/dashboard/summary`**
  - Functionally aliases the core logic invoked within `/overview` enabling backward compatibility or generalized metrics consumption.

- **`GET /api/dashboard/contributions`**
  - Leverages powerful Prisma Group-By operations grouping capital by `contributorName`. Triggers `_sum` aggregation strictly inside the relational layer guaranteeing massive bandwidth efficiency. Auto-populates static fallback colors (e.g., Red/Blue) if contributors omit them.

- **`GET /api/dashboard/stats`**
  - Instantly issues broad system-wide status telemetry. Calculates basic integers indicating total valid `Clients`, active [Invoices](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#262-288), specific [Pending](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.ts#262-288) Invoices, and un-rejected [Expenses](file:///Users/abc/Documents/backend/Backend/src/controllers/expense.controller.ts#97-167).

- **`GET /api/dashboard/chart-data`**
  - **Time-Series Logic (`transactionsData`):** Unrolls and flattens grouped arrays of daily transaction sums split intrinsically by `CREDIT` (Revenue) and `DEBIT` (Expenses).
  - **Bar Chart Logic (`barChartData`):** Compresses purely `PAID` expenses localized categorically around daily increments (`expenseDate`).
  - **Pie Chart Logic (`pieChartData`):** Implements dynamic summation of `amount` grouped precisely down to the string-level `category` taxonomy, transmitting proportional arrays featuring an automated percent distribution index.

- **`GET /api/dashboard/table/pending-invoices`**
  - Optimized datatable injection route querying only specific states: `PENDING`, `PARTIAL`, `OVERDUE`, `DRAFT`. Returns composite rows incorporating direct `client` entity names in a single streamlined payload.

- **`GET /api/dashboard/table/recent-transactions`**
  - Top-down `desc` chronological stream of raw ledger events globally. Features heavy relational `include` configurations appending associated `invoiceNumber` strings, literal `expense.title` details, or `contribution.contributorName` references seamlessly.

